# UI Guidance

`docs/UI_GUIDELINES.md` is the source of truth for spacing, typography, radius, colors, buttons, inputs, tables, dialogs, animations, and responsive behavior.

Also read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` before moving domain logic into shared UI.

Keep this rule short. Do not copy UI tokens or component recipes here.

## Non-Negotiables

- Use `@/components/ui/*` primitives for generic controls.
- Keep domain components under `components/dashboard/<feature>/`.
- Use lucide-react icons and sonner toasts.
- User-facing admin copy is Russian unless product docs say otherwise.
- Do not put domain logic in `components/ui/`.
